According to the author, many Mexicans were forced to leave Mexico because of the lack of opportunities to realize themselves.
Mexicans tend to blame those who have left, because they remind residents of the country of the difficult times.
Ruben Наваретте believes that the Mexicans American origin are torn between two cultures.
