Every day Анто down to the very bottom of the crater, where sulfur dioxide, rising from the depths of the Earth, hardens in contact with air.
Breaking off a huge chunks of sulphur, total weight of which can reach up to 70 kg, he puts them in two bamboo baskets, will place a basket on his shoulders and carries them up the steep stony road.
Up to the top of the volcano, the height of which is 2.386 meters, only 250 meters, but exhausted the laborers are required more than 40 minutes to get up at a snail's pace, with difficulty keeping balance and carefully picking a way to not trip and fall over a cliff.
They know that one wrong move could cost them their life, as it happened with one tourist from France, which collapsed a few years ago from the rocks Qavah-Иджена.
