Once on top, they are paving their way among the tourists that they are photographed, as if they were apes from the circus, and, tired of carrying the heavy baskets, walk three kilometres to the weights that the mining company has placed a little higher, at an altitude of 1.850 meters.
It is about SA Kandy Нгримби, the company, which operates since 1960, the volcano, and it is better not to say, of its employees, which it pays 662 Indonesian rupiah (5 eurocents) for each kilogram of sulphur.
Then it sells for around 10,000 rupees (83 eurocents) petrochemical industries, since this mineral is widespread in everyday life and is used for the manufacture of matches, fireworks, cosmetics, dynamite and even for bleaching of sugar.
"As the norm is carrying 70 kilograms, we earn about 46.000 rupees (3.8 euros) for each separate raids", " explains us Анто, which usually carries out three daily carrying.
He spends three hours on each of them and in the end feels shattered, but they allow him to accumulate 138.000 rupees (11,5 Euro) to the end of the day.
Although it seems мизером for such an inhuman effort, it is three times more than what he would have earned in the field.
"Daily wage miners is very high by local standards, where for the collection of coffee pay of 15,000 rupees (1,2 euros) per day and the average monthly earnings is equal to two million rupees (167 EUR) ", - explains the porter, who had previously worked as a bricklayer on the tourist island of Bali.
There his salary was 75.000 rupees (6,2 Euro) per day, and the plot was not so heavy, but Анто returned with his family in Баньюванги, a town not far from the volcano, for good reason, which in Indonesia is as devastating as sulphur: "I married a girl from Bali, where some of the Hindus, and brought her to Java, so she accepted Islam".
The Анто asthma, he breathed with difficulty, constantly coughing, and his eyes from the toxic gases
